rd a sticky horizontal bar on desktop and a swipeable rail on mobile, making navigation intuitive. I'm confirming the pages to be included and starting to consider the structure for `/company`, `/company/mission`, and `/company/leadership`.\n\n\n**Refining Page Content**\n\nI am now focusing on refining the content for the `/company` subpages, including `/company/partners`, `/company/advisors`, `/company/careers`, `/company/investors`, and `/company/media`. I am carefully integrating Dr. Ashish Chandra's role with placeholders for Executive Committee roles, while strictly avoiding invented profiles or fake names. I am also working on the `/company/locations` page, focusing on visual representations for Singapore, London, and India global hubs. I aim to create polished and realistic content, staying true to GFF AI's requirements.\n\n\n**Planning Design Elements**\n\nI'm now planning premium design elements for each `/company` subpage to make them stand out. I've begun listing three distinct elements for each page. The `/company` index will feature an animated SVG representing GFF's modular flow, a Bento grid showing the \"Garage Foundry Factory\" operating model, and a custom hero with a high-end photo of the executive committee. I'll also add secure contact gateways and specialized consultation options to `/company/contact` while including GFF AI brand assets and official boilerplate to ensure a proper press kit.\n\n\n**Detailing Page Components**\n\nI'm now detailing premium design elements. `/company/partners` will have a custom grid, a dynamic visual showing partner integration, and a premium CTA with motion reveal. For `/company/mission`, a narrative timeline, a tabbed value showcase, and a hero visual are planned. `/company/leadership` will feature a Dr. Ashish Chandra profile, an executive role carousel, and hover interactions. `/company/locations` is planned to show an interactive map, layered capability previews, and regional CTAs.\n\n\n**Outlining Specific 