{"ts":"2026-06-26T07:35:02.594Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Drafting the Design Plan**\n\nI'm pleased to report the initial build was flawless! I've shifted focus to drafting the internal design plan. I'm prioritizing outlining it directly in the chat, as requested, to ensure we capture all requirements. I'm eager to get this documented before I move on to writing code!\n\n\n**Defining the Page Narrative**\n\nI'm now deeply immersed in defining the narrative for each section. The goal is to convey GFF AI's unwavering credibility and global scale within 5 seconds. I'm focusing on crafting a compelling story for each page, from the `/company` overview highlighting operational excellence to `/locations` showcasing global deployment. The \"Architects of the Agent Economy\" concept should resonate clearly.\n\n\n**Outlining the Subpages**\n\nI'm now outlining the specific content for key subpages like `/company/partners`, `/company/advisors`, and `/company/careers`. I'm also considering the investor relations, media, and contact sections.\n\n**Designing the Visual Metaphor**\n\nThe visual metaphor is solidifying: a global matrix of interconnected nodes, powered by glowing conduits for data and memory. I'm imagining SVG diagrams with dark backgrounds and neon status indicators for a premium feel. Sharp typography is essential.\n\n**Deciding Layout Structure**\n\nI've decided on a sticky horizontal \"Company Hub\" for easy navigation across all subpages. Each will have its own unique layout. For instance, the `/company` page will feature a bento grid showcasing structural metrics.\n\n\n**Detailing the Sub-Pages**\n\nI'm deep into the specifics now, outlining `/company`'s subpages. I'm focusing on interactive elements: a vertical timeline for `/company/mission`, spotlight cards for `/company/leadership`, and an immersive `GlobalHubMap` for `/company/locations`. `/company/partners` will have an SVG architecture flow, while `/company/advisors` will feature a knowledge graph. Finally, `/company/careers` will use filterable path cards.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Mobile First**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the mobile strategy. I plan for elegant navigation on smaller screens, using swipeable rails or compact menus. Layouts will be fully responsive and collapse into a single column, with touch-friendly zones for all interactive elements.\n\nI've also identified the specific files I need to change or create for the company pages, like `CompanyNavigation.tsx` and all new page routes, ranging from the main profile at `app/company/page.tsx` to the new route at `app/careers/page.tsx`, which will simply re-export the original `/company/careers` page for legacy reasons.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T07:35:02.596Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"1ytd9bu2","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/components/inner-pages/CompanyNavigation.tsx","new_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport React, { useRef, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport Link from \"next/link\";\nimport { usePathname } from \"next/navigation\";\nimport { cn } from \"@/lib/utils\";\n\nconst NAV_ITEMS = [\n  { label: \"Profile\", href: \"/company\" },\n  { label: \"Mission\", href: \"/company/mission\" },\n  { label: \"Leadership\", href: \"/company/leadership\" },\n  { label: \"Locations\", href: \"/company/locations\" },\n  { label: \"Partners\", href: \"/company/partners\" },\n  { label: \"Advisors\", href: \"/company/advisors\" },\n  { label: \"Careers\", href: \"/company/careers\" },\n  { label: \"Investors\", href: \"/company/investors\" },\n  { label: \"Media\", href: \"/company/media\" },\n  { label: \"Contact\", href: \"/company/contact\" },\n];\n\nexport default function CompanyNavigation() {\n  const pathname = usePathname();\n  const activeRef = useRef<HTMLAnchorElement>(null);\n  const containerRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (activeRef.current && containerRef.current) {\n      const activeElement = activeRef.current;\n      const container = containerRef.current;\n      const activeRect = activeElement.getBoundingClientRect();\n      const containerRect = container.getBoundingClientRect();\n\n      if (\n        activeRect.left < containerRect.left ||\n        activeRect.right > containerRect.right\n      ) {\n        container.scrollTo({\n          left:\n            activeElement.offsetLeft -\n            container.clientWidth / 2 +\n            activeElement.clientWidth / 2,\n          behavior: \"smooth\",\n        });\n      }\n    }\n  }, [pathname]);\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"relative w-full border-b border-white/5 bg-black/40 backdrop-blur-[12px] z-20\">\n      <div className=\"max-w-[1795px] mx-auto px-6 lg:px-16\">\n        <div\n          ref={containerRef}\n          className=\"flex items-center gap-6 md:gap-8 overflow-x-auto no-scrollbar py-4\"\n        >\n          {NAV_ITEMS.map((item) => {\n            const isActive = pathname === item.href;\n            return (\n              <Link\n                key={item.href}\n                href={item.href}\n                ref={isActive ? activeRef : null}\n                className={cn(\n                  \"relative text-[12.5px] uppercase font-mono tracking-widest py-1 whitespace-nowrap transition-colors cursor-pointer shrink-0 select-none\",\n                  isActive\n                    ? \"text-[#009DFF] font-semibold\"\n                    : \"text-white/40 hover:text-white/80\"\n                )}\n              >\n                {item.label}\n                {isActive && (\n                  <span className=\"absolute bottom-[-17px] left-0 right-0 h-[2px] bg-gradient-to-r from-[#E4000F] to-[#009DFF]\" />\n                )}\n              </Link>\n            );\n          })}\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n"}}}
